quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,91,"And Hellfire will be brought forth for the deviators,"
  26,92,"And it will be said to them, "
  26,93,"Other than Allāh? Can they help you or help themselves?"
  27,64,"Is He [not best] who begins creation and then repeats it and who provides for you from the heaven and earth? Is there a deity with Allāh? Say, "
  27,65,"Say, "
  27,66,"Rather, their knowledge is arrested concerning the Hereafter. Rather, they are in doubt about it. Rather, they are, concerning it, blind."
  28,37,"And Moses said, ",1:[i.e., in this world or in the Hereafter.]
  28,38,"And Pharaoh said, ",1:[From which bricks are made.]
  28,39,"And he was arrogant, he and his soldiers, in the land, without right, and they thought that they would not be returned to Us."
  29,4,"Or do those who do evil deeds think they can outrun [i.e., escape] Us? Evil is what they judge."
  29,5,"Whoever should hope for the meeting with Allāh - indeed, the term [decreed by] Allāh is coming. And He is the Hearing, the Knowing."
  29,6,"And whoever strives only strives for [the benefit of] himself. Indeed, Allāh is Free from need of the worlds."